<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Vyacheslav Akimov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 24 May (ITAR-TASS) -- "Russia supports the 
unity and stability of Yemen". The ITAR-TASS correspondent was 
told today by a representative of the Russian Federation 
Ministry of Foreign Affairs that this was contained in a message 
from the Russian leadership which was conveyed to 'Ali 'Abdallah 
Salih, chairman of the Presidential Council of the Republic of 
Yemen, yesterday by the Russian ambassador to Yemen. 
  It notes in the message that Russia follows the development 
of events in Yemen attentively and is concerned over the 
continuing military operations and senseless fratricidal 
bloodshed, as a result of which hundreds of people have 
perished. Moscow, the message says, calls for a cease-fire and 
supports the unity of the entire people of Yemen. 

